comment: Hi guys, just a quick comment on the crap that you are receiving on twitter from the gang that have set themselves up as owners of the Depp justice movement. I was on twitter for a while and left because of these guys. There are many of us who support JD for years who are not on twitter bleating on about all they have done. Followers bow down to them & put them on pedestals, this is not healthy as imo results in people getting forced off twitter if they don't follow the narrative . I admire you guys for standing up for yourselves. Those on their high horses do not like to be challenged. A healthy movement is respectful & would never become a lynch mob. And I agree with you Colonel Kurt, JD would not agree with this behaviour. #JusticeForJohnnyDepp is a movement that exists much wider than twitter. Personally l believe that, twitter doesn't deserve all of JD's followers considering how they have treated him & Adam. Apologies if this is long winded. Keep doing what you are doing, you must be doing something right when you are ruffling feathers üòâ
